[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Patch [0m[33mResult[0m[39m===[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a libFuzzer timeout error occurring during fuzzing of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApache FontBox Type1 font parser. A patch was attempted that introduced parsing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimits and additional validation checks to prevent DoS attacks by limiting the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum number of subrs, charstrings, encoding entries, and dictionary search [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations. Despite these changes, the timeout error persists after applying the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, indicating that the root cause of the performance issue has not been [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddressed.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzing process reports [0m[32m"ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout"[0m[39m when testing the codebase. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis indicates that the fuzzer is encountering an execution path that takes an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive amount of time to complete, exceeding the configured timeout threshold. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe timeout occurs during the processing of Type1 font files, specifically within [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `org.apache.fontbox.type1.Type1Parser` class.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduces a new `Type1ParserLimits` class that defines maximum [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthresholds for various parsing operations:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_SUBRS`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_CHARSTRINGS`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES`: [0m[1;36m256[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_DICT_ENTRIES`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `MAX_DICT_SEARCH_ITERATIONS`: [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies several methods in the `Type1Parser` class:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Encoding parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`readEncoding` area, around line [0m[1;36m225[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds a counter `searchIterations` to track loop iterations while searching for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencoding start markers[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws an IOException if iterations exceed `MAX_DICT_SEARCH_ITERATIONS`[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds null check for peek token to prevent infinite loops[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds validation to limit encoding entries to `MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Private dictionary search [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m554[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds `privateSearchIterations` counter to limit search iterations[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws an IOException if the `[0m[35m/[0m[95mPrivate[0m[39m` dictionary is not found within [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_DICT_SEARCH_ITERATIONS`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Subrs reading [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m707[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates the length parameter against `MAX_SUBRS` before allocation[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds `entriesRead` counter to prevent reading more entries than allowed[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds bounds checking [0m[1;39m([0m[39mj >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before accessing the subrs array[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **OtherSubrs reading [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m802[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates the length parameter against `MAX_SUBRS`[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **CharStrings reading [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m830[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates the length parameter against `MAX_CHARSTRINGS`[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds `entriesRead` counter to prevent processing more entries than allowed[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same timeout error persists. This indicates that:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The limits imposed by the patch are either too high to prevent the timeout[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is occurring in a different code path not covered by the patch[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- There may be other performance bottlenecks such as expensive operations within [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe parsing logic itself [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., decryption operations, token reading, or data [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure operations[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Token Lexer Performance**: The `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethods are called frequently in loops. The lexer implementation should be examined[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor performance issues, especially when processing malformed or adversarial input.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Decrypt Operation**: The `[0m[1;35mdecrypt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcharstring.getData[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, CHARSTRING_KEY, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlenIV[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method is called for each charstring and subr. This cryptographic operation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould be a performance bottleneck if called excessively or with large data.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Unpatched Loops**: There may be other loops in the parser that are not covered[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the current patch. A comprehensive review of all loop structures in the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mType1Parser class is needed.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Token Reading Operations**: The `[0m[1;35mread[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method calls should be examined to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderstand their performance characteristics, particularly when dealing with [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed input.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Data Structure Operations**: The operations on `font.subrs`, `codeToName`, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother data structures should be analyzed for performance issues, especially when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthese structures grow large.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Buffer and Stream Operations**: The underlying input stream operations and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffering mechanisms should be examined, as inefficient I/O operations could [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontribute to timeouts.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Interaction with Other Components**: The integration between the lexer, token [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing, and font object construction should be reviewed to identify potential [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperformance issues in their interactions.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Additional Issue Log[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the additional issue log after the last patch attempt:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<additional_issue>[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95madditional_issue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Notes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All patch attempts are applied to the initial codebase. Reapply the the previous [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatches if needed.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If multiple different issues are present, all the issues must be resolved in a [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfontbox/src/test/java/org/apache/fontbox/type1/Type1LexerTest.jav[0m[1;92ma:137[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m151[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Timeout Issue[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the evaluation report and code snippets, I've identified that the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevious patch attempted to add iteration limits but the **root cause of the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loops was not properly addressed**. The timeout persists because:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Infinite Loop Vulnerability**: The core issue is in loops with the pattern [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`while [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdon't explicitly check for null tokens. When the lexer exhausts its input:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns null[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mpeekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returns false [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdue to null check[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `![0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse && [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` evaluates to true[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The loop continues infinitely, calling `[0m[1;35mnextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which returns null [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeatedly[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Two Critical Vulnerable Loops in Type1Parser**:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Line [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[39m in [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Searching for encoding start markers[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Line [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[39m in [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Searching for [0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[39m token[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The previous patch added iteration counters but didn't fix the fundamental [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnull-check issue**, so malformed input can still cause timeouts before reaching the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miteration limits.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Comprehensive Fix Strategy[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Fix Infinite Loop Vulnerabilities in Type1Parser[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m217[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChange the loop condition to explicitly check for null tokens BEFORE the negated [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcondition:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Before the while loop at line [0m[1;36m217[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mToken currentToken = [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentToken != null && [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.NAME[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcurrentToken.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"dup"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurrentToken.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"readonly"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurrentToken.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"def"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    currentToken = [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After the loop, check if we found the expected token[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentToken == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Unexpected end of tokens while searching for encoding [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mstart"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m640[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m644[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mApply the same fix pattern:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Replace the while loop at line [0m[1;36m640[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mToken currentToken = [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentToken != null && [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ![0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mlexer.peekKind[0m[1;39m([0m[39mToken.LITERAL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m && [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mcurrentToken.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"CharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    currentToken = [0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After the loop, check if we found the expected token[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurrentToken == null[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Unexpected end of tokens while searching for [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mCharStrings"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Keep Memory Allocation Protection [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom previous patch[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch correctly added validation for memory allocation in:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m709[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Validate length before allocating[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m779[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Validate length [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **[0m[1;35mreadOtherSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m759[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Validate length[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese protections should be **retained** with the Type1ParserLimits class.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Simplify Iteration Counting [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional Enhancement[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch added entriesRead counters in [0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhile these are good safeguards, they may not be necessary if the loop termination [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions are properly checked. However, they should be **retained as [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefense-in-depth** but with the proper null checks added to ensure loops terminate [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Remove Redundant Search Iteration Counters[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `searchIterations` and `privateSearchIterations` counters from the previous [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch can be **removed** since the proper null checks will naturally terminate the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops when tokens are exhausted. However, if retained for defense-in-depth, they [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be kept as secondary safeguards.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Why This Fix Works[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses Root Cause**: By explicitly checking `currentToken != null` in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop condition and storing `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` result in a variable, we prevent the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfinite loop scenario where null tokens cause the negated condition to always be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrue.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Follows Safe Pattern**: This matches the safe pattern used in [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m557[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m564[0m[39m for searching for [0m[32m"/Private"[0m[39m token, which explicitly checks [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`peekToken != null`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Proper Error Handling**: Throws IOException with descriptive messages when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens are exhausted unexpectedly, rather than looping infinitely.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: The fix doesn't change the parsing logic, only [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madds proper null checks to prevent infinite loops.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Combined with the memory allocation limits from the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevious patch, this provides multiple layers of protection against malformed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Reapply Type1ParserLimits class** from the previous patch[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Fix the two vulnerable loops** in [0m[1;35mreadEncoding[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mparseBinary[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicit null checks[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Retain memory allocation validation** in [0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mreadOtherSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Optionally retain entriesRead counters** in [0m[1;35mreadSubrs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m[1;35mreadCharStrings[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas secondary safeguards[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Remove or adjust search iteration counters** since proper null checks will [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mterminate loops naturally[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Expected Outcome[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout error will be resolved because loops will properly terminate when [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokens are exhausted[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Memory allocation DoS attacks are prevented by the validation limits[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parser remains forgiving for legitimate fonts while rejecting malformed [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madversarial input[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Existing functionality is preserved - all valid Type1 fonts that parsed before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill still parse correctly[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mERROR[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===[0m[33mIssue[0m[39m===[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reported a libFuzzer timeout error when testing the codebase. A [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was applied to the `Type1Parser.java` file that introduced parsing limits and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional validation checks to prevent denial-of-service [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m attacks through [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexcessive resource allocation. However, after applying the patch, the same [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer timeout error persists, indicating that the timeout issue was not [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved by these changes.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a timeout error detected by libFuzzer during fuzzing [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperations. This typically occurs when the parser enters an infinite loop, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexperiences excessive computational complexity, or processes input data in a manner[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat takes an unreasonable amount of time to complete. The error message provides [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mminimal detail, indicating only that a timeout threshold was exceeded during [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduces several defensive programming measures to the Type1Parser [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addition of Type1ParserLimits class**: A new inner class defining maximum [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimits for:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_SUBRS`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m subroutines[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_CHARSTRINGS`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m character strings[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES`: [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m encoding entries[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `MAX_OTHERSUBRS`: [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m other subroutines[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Encoding parsing improvements** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modified the while loop to store `[0m[1;35mpeekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` result in a variable to avoid [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeated calls[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added null checking for the current token[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation to throw an IOException if the end of tokens is reached [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munexpectedly[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a check to prevent more than `MAX_ENCODING_ENTRIES` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m256[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from being [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessed[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **CharStrings search improvements** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m660[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar token handling improvements with null checking[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation to throw an IOException if CharStrings is not found before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of tokens[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Subrs validation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m738[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation to ensure the Subrs count is within bounds [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to `MAX_SUBRS`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added range checking when setting subroutine values [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchecking for `j >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **OtherSubrs validation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m796[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation to ensure the OtherSubrs count is within bounds [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_OTHERSUBRS`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **CharStrings validation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m824[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation to ensure the CharStrings count is within bounds [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_CHARSTRINGS`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Patch[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe libFuzzer timeout error persists after applying the patch, which indicates [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is not caused by excessive memory allocation from large array sizes[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout is not caused by processing too many encoding entries, subrs, or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharstrings within the modified code paths[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The root cause of the timeout likely lies in a different area of the code or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvolves a different type of infinite loop/complexity issue[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo identify the actual cause of the timeout, the following areas should be [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvestigated:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **The Type1Lexer class**: The parser heavily relies on `[0m[1;35mlexer.peekToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mlexer.nextToken[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls. The lexer implementation should be examined for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotential infinite loops or inefficient token processing.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Other while loops in Type1Parser**: The patch modified two specific while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops, but there may be other loops in the parser that could cause timeouts when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing malformed or malicious input.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The [0m[1;35mdecrypt[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method**: Called in multiple places [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., line [0m[1;36m777[0m[39m in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatched code[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for processing charstring data. This method should be examined for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputational complexity issues.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Recursive parsing patterns**: The parser may have recursive calls or nested [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing operations that could lead to deep call stacks or exponential time [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomplexity with certain input patterns.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Token stream handling**: The overall token stream processing logic should be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreviewed to ensure there are mechanisms to detect and handle circular references, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed structure definitions, or other patterns that could cause infinite [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Input preprocessing**: The font file preprocessing and reading logic before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtokenization should be examined to determine if certain input patterns could cause [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe lexer itself to hang or process inefficiently.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **The entire parsing workflow**: A holistic review of how the Type1Font parsing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprogresses from file input through tokenization to final parsed structure would [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelp identify where the fuzzer input causes the timeout.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fact that the timeout persists despite adding limits suggests the issue is in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe control flow logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39minfinite loops[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m rather than resource exhaustion, or occurs [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min code sections not covered by the patch.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
